d to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts/","name":"Legal Consultancy in Turkey with Foreign Experts - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-11T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-11T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Legal Consultancy in Turkey with Foreign Experts - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-11T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-11T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Explore legal and consulting services in Turkey with the help of foreign experts. Understand the regulations and opportunities for international professionals looking to study or work in the legal field.","name":"Legal Consultancy in Turkey with Foreign Experts - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this post, we&#8217;ll take a detailed look at topics such as legal consultancy in Turkey, the possibilities for foreign experts to practice law, career opportunities, and the role of international legal specialists.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-hukuk-egitimi-uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-firsatlar" class="wp-block-heading">Legal Education in Turkey: Opportunities for International Students</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quality Educational Institutions</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is home to many world-renowned universities such as <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/bogazici-universitesi/">Boğaziçi Üniversitesi</a>, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/koc-universitesi/">Koç Üniversitesi</a>, and <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/istanbul-universitesi-2/">İstanbul Üniversitesi</a>. These universities offer high-quality education in the field of law and hold international accreditation. By studying at these institutions, students have the opportunity to both gain academic knowledge and build international connections.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Affordable Costs</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The annual tuition fees at Turkish universities are quite affordable compared to universities in the US and Europe. For example, annual tuition fees generally range between 1,000 – 4,000 USD. This makes Turkey an economical option for international students.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Richness</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As a country where different cultures coexist, Turkey offers a rich cultural experience. While studying in Turkey, international students have the opportunity to get to know the local culture and discover different traditions. Additionally, Turkey&#8217;s historical and natural beauties offer many places for students to explore.</p>
<h2 id="yabanci-uyruklular-turkiyede-avukatlik-yapabilir-mi" class="wp-block-heading">Can Foreign Nationals Practice Law in Turkey?</h2>
<p>In Turkey, <strong>the legal profession is open only to Turkish citizens</strong>. According to the Attorneyship Law No. 1136, to become a lawyer, one must be a citizen of the Republic of Turkey, a graduate of a law faculty, and fulfill the internship requirements.</p>
<p>Foreign nationals <strong>cannot practice law independently</strong> in Turkey. However, in some cases:</p>
<ul>
<li>They can provide <strong>consultancy</strong> services (especially regarding the law of their home country).</li>
<li>They can work as <strong>foreign consultants in international law firms</strong> operating in Turkey.</li>
<li>Individuals with dual citizenship can practice law if they meet the Turkish citizenship requirement.</li>
</ul>
<p>In other words, foreigners cannot become lawyers directly registered with a bar association in Turkey; however, they can provide <strong>limited legal consultancy</strong>.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-hukuk-ve-danismanlik-alaninda-kariyer-olanaklari" class="wp-block-heading">Career Opportunities in Law and Consultancy in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers many career opportunities in the field of law and consultancy. In particular, the representative offices of international companies in Turkey, foreign investors, and international law firms create significant opportunities for those who want to pursue a career in law.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Career Opportunities</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Law Firms</strong>: You can gain experience in various legal fields by working in national and international law firms in Turkey.</li>
<li><strong>Corporate Law</strong>: You can specialize in areas such as commercial law, labor law, and contract law by working in the legal departments of international companies.</li>
<li><strong>Government Institutions</strong>: There are opportunities to pursue a career in legal consultancy and public law within government institutions in Turkey.</li>
<li><strong>Academic Career</strong>: Those who want to pursue an academic career in law can work as lecturers or research assistants at universities.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="uluslararasi-hukuk-uzmani-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">What is an International Law Specialist?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An international law specialist is a person who has specialized in the field of international law and is knowledgeable in this area. These experts can provide consultancy on subjects such as international relations, human rights, commercial law, and environmental law. International law specialists generally work in the following areas:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Law Firms</strong>: They provide consultancy services in international law firms, informing clients about the requirements of international law.</li>
<li><strong>Government Institutions</strong>: They support government institutions in the preparation and implementation of international treaties and agreements.</li>
<li><strong>International Organizations</strong>: They work in international organizations such as the United Nations and the European Union, ensuring the implementation of international law.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="hukuk-islerinde-danismanlik-yapan-kisi-kimdir" class="wp-block-heading">What is a Legal Consultant?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A legal consultant is an expert who guides individuals or institutions on legal issues. These individuals are generally called lawyers, legal consultants, or specialists. Legal consultants can provide services in the following areas:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Contract Drafting</strong>: They assist clients with drafting and reviewing contracts.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Advice</strong>: They inform clients about legal issues and offer potential solutions.</li>
<li><strong>Litigation Processes</strong>: They represent clients in court and provide guidance throughout the litigation process.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Legal consultants are usually specialized in a specific area of law and have in-depth knowledge in that field.</p>
<h2 id="sonuc" class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey attracts international students with its excellent educational opportunities, cultural richness, and affordable living costs. Studying law in Turkey not only imparts academic knowledge but also opens doors to a career in international law. Foreign nationals have opportunities to develop their careers through the various legal consultancy roles available in Turkey. Studying in Turkey is a journey that offers a chance for both personal and professional growth.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3>Who can provide legal consultancy?</h3>
<p>In Turkey, anyone with a law degree can provide <strong>limited consultancy</strong>, even if they are not registered with a bar association.</p>
<h3>Can a foreign lawyer work in Turkey?</h3>
<p>Foreign lawyers can work as <strong>consultants in international law firms</strong> in Turkey, but they cannot be independent lawyers.</p>
<h3>What is international legal consultancy?</h3>
<p>It is providing <strong>consultancy services</strong> on the legal systems of different countries and international agreements.</p>
<h3>Who is Turkey&#8217;s top lawyer?</h3>
<p>The &#8220;top&#8221; lawyer depends on the criteria used; well-known and influential lawyers in Turkey, such as <strong>Celal Ülgen</strong> or <strong>Haluk Kırca</strong>, are notable examples.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-06-11T07:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:53:08Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'legal-consultancy-in-turkey-with-foreign-experts' );
