<h3 data-start="0" data-end="50">How many people receive a salary from the state in Turkey?</h3>
<p data-start="52" data-end="298" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">According to SGK data, <strong>16,437,000 people in Turkey receive a salary from the state</strong>. Of these, 11,826,000 are retirees, and 4,278,000 receive widow&#8217;s and orphan&#8217;s pensions. In the first 7 months of 2024, <strong>1.428 trillion TL</strong> was paid to these individuals.</p>
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-WEB:b4d53112-d8dd-402a-8555-40c6278ee8fa-14" data-testid="conversation-turn-30" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
