y Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey/","name":"Social Security for Foreign Employees in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-07T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-07T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Social Security for Foreign Employees in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-07T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-07T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about the social security system in Turkey and the rights of foreign employees. Read our article for more details!","name":"Social Security for Foreign Employees in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security system in Turkey offers an important framework for both local and foreign employees. In this article, we will cover how the social security system in Turkey works, the rights of foreign employees, premium contributions, healthcare services, retirement processes, and other key points you need to know. Understanding the social security system in Turkey is crucial for both employees and employers.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-sosyal-guvenlik-sistemi-nedir-ve-nasil-isler" class="wp-block-heading">What is the Social Security System in Turkey and How Does It Work?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s social security system is a structure established to ensure the social and economic security of employees and their families. This system covers various areas such as healthcare services, retirement, unemployment insurance, and social assistance. The social security system in Turkey is managed by the Social Security Institution (SGK).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Key Components of the Social Security System</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Health Insurance</strong>: Allows employees to benefit from healthcare services.</li>
<li><strong>Pension Insurance</strong>: Provides financial support to employees during their retirement.</li>
<li><strong>Unemployment Insurance</strong>: Offers financial support to unemployed workers for a certain period.</li>
<li><strong>Social Assistance</strong>: Support provided to individuals with insufficient financial means.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security system is designed to prevent employees from suffering in situations such as work accidents, illness, old age, and unemployment.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also benefit from our article on <a title="Work Ethic and Professional Ethical Standards in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-is-ahlaki-ve-etik-standartlar/">Work Ethic and Professional Ethical Standards in Turkey</a>.</p>
<h2 id="yabanci-calisanlar-icin-turkiyede-sosyal-guvenlik-haklari" class="wp-block-heading">Social Security Rights for Foreign Employees in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees can benefit from social security rights during their employment in Turkey. These rights include the protection and support provided by the Turkish social security system.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Rights of Foreign Employees</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Healthcare Services</strong>: Foreign employees can access healthcare services as long as they are registered with the SGK.</li>
<li><strong>Pension Rights</strong>: Foreign employees may be entitled to a pension after working in Turkey for a specific period.</li>
<li><strong>Unemployment Insurance</strong>: In case of job loss, they can benefit from unemployment insurance under certain conditions.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security rights of foreign employees may vary depending on their duration of employment in Turkey and their registration status with the SGK.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also take a look at our article on <a title="Salary Structures and Negotiation Processes in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-maas-yapilari-pazarlik-surecleri/">Salary Structures and Negotiation Processes in Turkey</a>.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-calisan-yabancilar-icin-sosyal-guvenlik-primleri-ve-odemeleri" class="wp-block-heading">Social Security Premiums and Contributions for Foreigners Working in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Social security premiums for foreign employees are paid by their employers in Turkey. These premiums are necessary to protect the employees&#8217; social security rights.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Premium Contribution Processes</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Premium Rate</strong>: Social security premium rates are calculated based on the employee&#8217;s gross salary. As of 2023, the total premium rate is approximately 34.5%. This rate is shared between the employer and the employee.</li>
<li><strong>Payment Periods</strong>: Premiums must be paid regularly every month. Employers are obligated to report their employees&#8217; premiums to the SGK.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security premiums for foreign employees must be paid regularly throughout their employment in Turkey.</p>
<h2 id="sosyal-guvenlik-sistemi-kapsaminda-yabancilarin-saglik-hizmetleri" class="wp-block-heading">Healthcare Services for Foreigners under the Social Security System</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees have the right to benefit from healthcare services during their employment in Turkey. These services are provided by the SGK.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Accessing Healthcare Services</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Hospitals</strong>: As long as they are registered with the SGK, foreign employees can receive healthcare services from state hospitals and some private hospitals.</li>
<li><strong>Family Doctor</strong>: Foreign employees can also receive healthcare from family doctors. Family doctors provide primary healthcare services.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For foreign employees to benefit from healthcare services, they must be registered with the SGK and their premium payments must be made regularly.</p>
<h2 id="yabanci-calisanlar-icin-turkiyede-emeklilik-ve-gecmisteki-haklar" class="wp-block-heading">Retirement in Turkey for Foreign Employees</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees may be entitled to a pension after working in Turkey for a certain period. The retirement process varies depending on the duration of work and the premiums paid.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Retirement Conditions</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Duration of Work</strong>: To be eligible for retirement, foreign employees must have paid premiums for at least 7,200 days in Turkey.</li>
<li><strong>Age Requirement</strong>: Foreign employees must reach a certain age to retire. As of 2023, the retirement age is 58 for women and 60 for men.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To qualify for retirement rights in Turkey, foreign employees must complete the required number of premium days and meet the age requirement.</p>
<h2 id="yabanci-calisanlarin-turkiyede-sosyal-guvenlik-sistemi-ile-ilgili-bilmesi-gerekenler" class="wp-block-heading">What Foreign Employees Need to Know About the Social Security System in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees should be informed about the social security system in Turkey. This information is important both for protecting their rights and for better understanding the social security processes.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Key Things to Know</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Registration Process</strong>: Foreign employees must be registered with the SGK from the moment they start their job.</li>
<li><strong>Premium Payments</strong>: Premiums must be paid regularly every month. Otherwise, social security rights may be affected.</li>
<li><strong>Statement of Service</strong>: Foreign employees can obtain a statement of service from the SGK to check their number of premium days.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This information will help foreign employees better understand the social security system in Turkey.</p>
<h2 id="sonuc" class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security system in Turkey provides significant protection for both local and foreign employees. Foreign employees can benefit from social security rights such as healthcare services, pension rights, and unemployment insurance. It is crucial for foreign employees considering working in Turkey to understand the social security system and their rights, both for their personal and professional development. With the social security benefits it offers, Turkey presents an attractive working environment for foreign employees.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How does the social security system in Turkey work?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The social security system in Turkey ensures the protection of employees in various areas such as health, retirement, unemployment, and social assistance. It is managed by the Social Security Institution (SGK).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What social security rights do foreign employees have in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees can benefit from social security rights such as healthcare services, pension rights, and unemployment insurance.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much are the social security premiums?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Social security premiums for foreign employees are calculated based on their gross salary, and the total premium rate is approximately 34.5%. This rate is shared between the employer and the employee.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How can foreign employees access healthcare services?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As long as they are registered with the SGK, foreign employees can receive healthcare services from state hospitals and some private hospitals.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How can foreign employees qualify for a pension?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign employees must have paid premiums for at least 7,200 days in Turkey and reach a certain age. As of 2023, the retirement age is 58 for women and 60 for men.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-06-07T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:53:01Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'social-security-for-foreign-employees-in-turkey';
